LAGOS – A suspected land grabber and thug, Oluwatosin Jacob, has been arrested by the operatives of Lagos State Police Command. Oluwatosin was arrested durimg the invasion of 6th Avenue area of FESTAC town by armed thugs. Daily Independent gathered that the arrest of the suspect occurred less than two weeks after another land thug, Ayo Olatuniji, was arrested in the same area by policemen from the Area ‘M’ Police Command, Idimu. It was gathered that the arrested suspect and others, who escaped from the scene, had last week invaded a construction site in FESTAC Town and attempted to cause breakdown of law and order. -Advertisement- Residents of the area were said to have quickly alerted the police at FESTAC Town Divisional headquarters, where policemen were mobilised to the area. A labourer, who spoke on condition of anonymity said, “We were working on site, when some thugs came to attack us. “One of them shot into the air and we ran into different directions but luckily, the police arrived and arrested one of them, while others escaped.” The labourer also continued, “When they searched him, they found a lot of charms with him. “He could not explain what he was doing with the charms in that place. He was taken away to FESTAC police station. POLL ” The police in the state had last week confirmed the arrest of some suspected land thugs in the area. Ayo Olatuniji, one of the suspects, who were charged to court, had claimed to have been recruited by a certain T.J. and Oluomo. The police are still on the trail of T.J. and Oluomo, when another set of thugs invaded the FESTAC community. Efforts to speak with the image maker in charge of the state Police Command, Benjamin Hundeyin, failed as calls to his mobile phone lines were not answered as at the time of filing this report .